@startuml
title Sequence: Authentication & JWT Flow

participant "Frontend" as FE
participant "Public Routes" as ROUTES
participant "Accounts Service" as ACC_SVC
participant "Auth Service" as AUTH_SVC
participant "JWT Strategy" as JWT
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
database "JWT Cache" as CACHE

FE ->> ROUTES: POST /login {email, password}
ROUTES ->> ACC_SVC: findByEmail(email)
ACC_SVC ->> DB: SELECT * FROM accounts WHERE email
DB -->> ACC_SVC: account record
ROUTES ->> AUTH_SVC: validatePassword(input, hash)
AUTH_SVC ->> AUTH_SVC: bcrypt.compare()
AUTH_SVC -->> ROUTES: valid
ROUTES ->> JWT: generateTokenPair(id, email)
JWT ->> CACHE: store accessToken (15m)
JWT ->> CACHE: store refreshToken (7d)
JWT -->> ROUTES: tokens
ROUTES -->> FE: {accessToken, refreshToken}

FE ->> ROUTES: GET /accommodations\nHeader: Authorization: Bearer <token>
ROUTES ->> JWT: validateToken(token)
JWT ->> CACHE: getToken()
CACHE -->> JWT: token data
JWT ->> JWT: verify signature
JWT -->> ROUTES: valid
ROUTES -->> FE: data

note right of AUTH_SVC
  Uses bcrypt.compare()
  Sensitive operation - no plain password in logs
end note

note right of JWT
  Algorithm: HS256
  Payload: {id, email, userType}
  Secret: process.env.JWT_SECRET
end note

note right of CACHE
  In-memory with TTL
  Access token: 15 minutes
  Refresh token: 7 days
end note

@enduml
